<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-02T00:14:00-05:00" n="586" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/252.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santa Elena, Ecuador</hi></placeName>, <lb/>
                                <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1912-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1912-02-02T00:00:00-05:14"><hi rend="italic">Not
                                        dated</hi></date><hi rend="smallcaps">; received February
                                    13, 1912</hi>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Request <hi rend="italic">Maryland</hi> be held Santa Elena until my
                            arrival Washington, but no objection to temporary trip Panama for
                            supplies provided <hi rend="italic">Yorktown</hi> remains Ecuadorian
                            waters during absence <hi rend="italic">Maryland</hi>. Strongly urge and
                            recommend Captain Cordier, who is in touch with political situation,
                            remain with warship.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Young.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>